MALAYSIA DAYBOOK: CIMB, Maybank to Commence RHB Takeover Talks

-- B y   B a r r y   P o r t e r
-- 
2011-05-31T21:09:39Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-31/malaysia-daybook-cimb-maybank-to-commence-rhb-takeover-talks.html
CIMB Group Holdings Bhd. (CIMB MK)
and Malayan Banking Bhd. (MAY MK) won separate Malaysian central
bank approval to begin competing merger negotiations with RHB
Capital Bhd. (RHBC MK), triggering a potential takeover battle
to create  Southeast Asia ’s biggest bank.  The combined capitalization of CIMB and RHB would be $27.3
billion, based on yesterday’s closing prices. Maybank could
boost its market worth to $28.8 billion, which would exceed the
$27.7 billion value for  Singapore ’s DBS Group Holdings Ltd., the
region’s largest lender.  WHAT TO WATCH:
* Changes to MSCI  Malaysia  Index: Malaysia Airports Holdings Bhd.
(MAHB MK), Malaysia Marine and Heavy Engineering Bhd. (MMHE MK),
and UEM Land Holdings Bhd. (ULHB MK) added, Malaysian Airline
System Bhd. (MAS MK) dropped from today.
* Axiata briefing after annual meeting at 12:30 p.m.  KEY EARNINGS:
* Axiata Group Bhd. (AXIATA MK) 1Q net income fell to 548.4
million ringgit from 921.5 million ringgit a year earlier.
* Maxis Bhd. (MAXIS MK) 1Q net income fell to 539 million
ringgit from 552 million ringgit a year earlier.
* MMC Corp. (MMC MK) 1Q profit rose to 43 million ringgit from
33.2 million ringgit.
* Sunway Holdings Bhd. (SGW MK) 1Q net income rose to 43.2
million ringgit from 39.9 million ringgit.  MARKETS:
* Malaysia’s FTSE Bursa Malaysia KLCI Index rose 1 percent.
* The MSCI Asia Pacific Index increased 1.5 percent.
* The  Dow Jones Industrial Average  gained 1 percent.
* Palm oil August-delivery futures advanced 0.4 percent to 3,393
ringgit a metric ton.  BTV HIGHLIGHTS (KL time):
*7:40 a.m. David Winters: Wintergreen Advisers, CEO
*8:10 a.m. Jesse Lentchner: BTIG Asia-Pacific, CEO
*8:40 a.m. Taimur Baig: Deutsche Bank, Asia Economics Director
*9:10 a.m. Dariusz Kowalczyk, Credit Agricole, Economist
*9:40 a.m. John Rothfield, BAML, Director of Economics  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
